## TL;DR — The Oval Diamond Solitaire in {{year}}

The oval solitaire is the most-searched engagement ring style for the third consecutive year. The reason is simple: an oval diamond in a solitaire setting offers the largest face-up appearance, the most finger elongation, and the cleanest aesthetic of any diamond-and-setting combination. There is no halo inflating the look, no pavé competing for attention — just the stone.

**The best entry-level oval solitaire ring:** [Classic Four Prong in 14K Yellow Gold at $870](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/classic-four-prong-solitaire-engagement-ring-in-14k-yellow-gold-item-203257?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) + a [2ct GIA G-VS2 oval](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?Shape=Oval&Carats=2&Color=G&Clarity=VS2&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) at [$17,480](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?Shape=Oval&Carats=2&Color=G&Clarity=VS2&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) = **[$18,350 total](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?ShapeID=Oval&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**.

**The most-reviewed solitaire on Blue Nile:** [Classic Six-Prong at $1,000](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/classic-six-prong-solitaire-engagement-ring-in-14k-yellow-gold-item-203272?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — 1,894 reviews.

**The contrarian truth:** The solitaire is the hardest setting to hide behind. No halo, no pavé, no side stones to distract from a weak diamond. Buyers who choose the solitaire and buy a mediocre stone regret it more than any other ring style. The setting demands the best stone you can afford.

