## Oval Diamond Solitaire Necklace

The oval diamond solitaire is not limited to rings. The same stone-forward logic applies to pendants. A [GIA G-VS2 oval solitaire pendant](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-pendants?ShapeID=Oval&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) on a delicate yellow gold chain is one of the most wearable fine jewelry pieces available — it pairs with the ring without competing, and the oval shape creates a longer, more flattering neck line than a round stone pendant.

For an oval diamond solitaire necklace, the same 4C priorities apply: G+ color, VS2+ clarity, and strong cut proportions. At pendant scale (0.5–1.5ct), the price range is [$3,420–$10,840](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-pendants?ShapeID=Oval&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) for GIA-certified natural ovals.

